            <V n="text" t="single">
              <T n="single">0xC568FDEA<!--String: "The adventure markings that Gibbi Point once had—there's definitely one set in Wanderwood Wilds—well, I find the story of them to be absolutely fascinating in terms of how it speaks to the changing dynamic Sims have with this area.\n\nYou can see it as a negative in that Sims sometimes visited this lush, verdant area and felt it necessary to put their mark on it...or you can try to look at it through a lens of neutrality in that Sims have now arrived at a place where they show more respect and interest in the world they're a part of, but these traces of prior adventurers remain. I'm just excited to talk about history and the stories of Gibbi Point in general—the good, the bad, and the in-between!"--></T>
